# WKInterfaceDeviceBatteryState.unknown

**Case**

An unknown battery-charging state.

## Declaration

```swift
case unknown
```

## Discussion

When the device’s [doc://com.apple.watchkit/documentation/WatchKit/WKInterfaceDevice/isBatteryMonitoringEnabled] property is set to [doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/Swift/false], its [doc://com.apple.watchkit/documentation/WatchKit/WKInterfaceDevice/batteryState] property is set to [doc://com.apple.watchkit/documentation/WatchKit/WKInterfaceDeviceBatteryState/unknown].

## Battery States

- **WKInterfaceDeviceBatteryState.charging**: The device is connected to a charger, but its battery charge is under 100%.
- **WKInterfaceDeviceBatteryState.full**: The device is connected to a charger, and its battery is charged to 100%.
- **WKInterfaceDeviceBatteryState.unplugged**: The device is not connected to a charger and is running on battery power.
